	"keywords": "sca, stripe, Node, Nodejs, React, Reactjs, 3DS2, 3DS, psd2",
	"description": "What are PSD2, SCA, and 3DS?\nPSD2\nThe second Payment Services Directive (PSD2) is an EU directive announced in\n2015. The goal of PSD2 is to protect people when they pay online, promote open\nbanking [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_banking], and make cross-border\nEuropean payment services safer. It went into effect September of 2019.\n\nSCA\nStrong Customer Authentication (SCA) is a requirement of the PSD2\n[https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?uri&#x3D;uriserv:OJ.L_.2018.069.01.0023.01.ENG&amp;",
	"headline": "How to implement 3DS2 with Stripe for SCA compliance under PSD2 in Europe",
